  "prompt": "Can you be a pilot if you wear glasses?",
  "response": "Yes, you can be a pilot if you wear glasses, with some conditions:\n\n1. For civilian pilots:\n- Vision can be corrected to 20/20 with glasses or contact lenses\n- Different vision requirements exist for private and commercial pilot licenses\n- Annual medical exams ensure continued vision standards\n\n2. For military pilots:\n- Vision requirements are typically more stringent\n- Corrective surgery like LASIK can sometimes help meet vision standards\n- Each branch of military service has specific vision requirements\n\n3. General requirements:\n- Glasses/contacts must provide clear, stable vision\n- No significant vision impairment beyond correctable limits\n- Must pass regular vision and medical examinations\n\n4. Types of pilot roles allowing glasses:\n- Commercial airline pilots\n- Private pilots\n- Charter pilots\n- Flight instructors\n\nThe key is that your vision can be corrected to meet the required standards for safe flying.",
